The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Aug. 29: The benchmark sensex today surged 516 points, the biggest rise in four weeks, on all-round buying, particularly in interest sensitive banking and realty stocks, after inflation saw a decline yesterday. Marketmen said bourses ignored a slower 7.9 per cent GDP expansion as investors felt the growth rate was on expected line after a tight monetary policy by the Reserve Bank of India.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug. 29: Larsen amp; Toubro (L amp;T) may raise up to $400 million debt in the current fiscal to fund expansion. It could be syndicated loan or a private placement of debt, L amp;T chief financial officer Y.M. Deosthaleehe said.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 29: Pfizer has won a legal battle in Denmark in its patent litigation over anti-cholesterol drug Lipitor with Ranbaxy. The court ruled that the basic patent, which expires in November 2011, would be infringed by Ranbaxys generic atorvastatin product.                                                                                                                         
